e the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"de","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of any of the given names beginning with the letter <i>D-</i> (  compare  Jay   and   Kay  ), in particular   Dorothy .  It is also used as an independent name, and may in some cases be associated with the River Dee (  compare  Clyde  )."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"*E ROBERT de Hanham had at least 1 son with Agnes de Hamaps."},"et":{"–":"Surnud","–Female":"Surnud","1322–1391":"1322–1391","–Male":"Surnud","1322":"1322","about 1322":"umbes 1322","1391":"1391","Hanham, Gloucestershire, England":"Hanham, Gloucestershire, England"},"fi":{"–":"Kuollut","–Female":"Kuollut","1322–1391":"1322–1391","–Male":"Kuollut","1322":"1322","about 1322":"noin 1322","1391":"1391","Hanham, Gloucestershire, England":"Hanham, Gloucestershire, England"},"fr":{"–":"Décédé","–Female":"Décédée","1322–1391":"1322–1391","–Male":"Décédé","1322":"1322","about 1322":"environ 1322","1391":"1391","Hanham, Gloucestershire, England":"Hanham, Gloucestershire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"*E ROBERT de Hanham a eu au moins 1 fils avec Agnes de Hamaps."},"de":{"–":"Verstorben","–Female":"Verstorben","1322–1391":"1322–1391","–Male":"Verstorben","1322":"1322","about 1322":"um 1322","1391":"1391","Hanham, Gloucestershire, England":"Hanham, Gloucestershire, England","lifeSummary":"*E ROBERT de Hanham hatte mit Agnes de Hamaps mindestens 1 Sohn."},"ht":{"–":"Desede","–Female":"Desede","1322–1391":"1322–1391","–Male":"